    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL - SHIMMING
        PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED BEARINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1302008" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="6">
        <title>SHIMMING PROCEDURE FOR TAPERED BEARINGS</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The shimming procedure can be done in the horizontal or vertical position. The procedure is done
                    the same.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Shims must be aligned properly or else the rear bearing cover may be damaged when final torque is
                    applied.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft straps. Make sure a 0.100 countershaft rear bearing shim is
                installed (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p3">Figure 253</hotlnk>). Be sure the countershaft rear bearing races are seated
                in the bearing bores.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p3" filename="../figg13/g13020p3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 253. Countershaft Rear Bearing Shim</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install two (2) clean 3/8" x 1" bolts without washers directly across from each other in
                each bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p4">Figure 254</hotlnk>). Tapped holes in auxiliary case must be free of thread
                adhesive.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p4" filename="../figg13/g13020p4.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 254. Bearing Cover Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the bolts to 7 in-lbs. (0.8 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p5">Figure 255</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p5" filename="../figg13/g13020p5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 255. Tighten Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not install the countershaft rear bearing cover gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the output shaft six (6) times clockwise, then six (6) times counterclockwise to seat
                the countershaft rear bearings. Use a feeler gauge, as close to each bolt location as possible, and
                measure the gap between the countershaft rear bearing cover and the auxiliary case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p6">Figure 256</hotlnk>). Record the measurements. Using the average measurement,
                refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl1302009">Chart 1</hotlnk>
                Chart , to identify the proper shim.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p6" filename="../figg13/g13020p6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 256. Measure Gap</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft rear bearing cover and gauging shim.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the selected shim on the rear countershaft bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p7">Figure 257</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p7" filename="../figg13/g13020p7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 257. Rear Countershaft Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a new gasket on countershaft rear bearing cover mounting surface (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p7">Figure 257</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the countershaft rear bearing cover over the new gasket.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Eaton/Fuller Sealant #71205 or Loctite 242 to the retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020p8">Figure 258</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020p8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020p8" filename="../figg13/g13020p8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 258. Apply Sealant Loctite</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the retaining bolts and tighten to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;m).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Repeat steps 1-8 for the other countershaft rear bearing cover.</para>
        </step1>
